The Senate has suspended its screening of the ministerial nominees to enable the Senators go on a short break. The plenary is expected to resume at 2pm. However, before going on break the Red Chamber had screened former Minister of Power, Works and Housing, Babatunde Raji Fashola (Lagos), who was well grilled by the Senators, Gbemisola Saraki Saraki (Kwara) and Dr. Mohammed Mahmoud (Kaduna State).